user_prompt_template:
As of {as_of}, does {company}'s capital allocation (R&D/capex trajectory, stated strategy, management commentary) suggest genuine, credible reinvestment into future growth, rather than declining reinvestment / harvesting cash from a maturing business? Score 2 (credibly reinvesting for growth), 1 (mixed/unclear), or 0 (harvesting, declining reinvestment) — based only on what was true and knowable as of {as_of}.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

As of {as_of}, does {company} still have substantial, realistic runway to keep growing for years (low penetration of a large/growing addressable market, clear expansion vectors) or is it already dominant/saturated in a market that isn't itself growing much further? Score 2 (real multi-year runway), 1 (some runway, getting mature), or 0 (near-saturated, limited runway) — based only on what was true and knowable as of {as_of}.

Company situation:
{company_brief}
